your webbrowser and navigate to http://localhost:8080/ide/\n\n## Licenses\n\nThis project is a collection of modules and open source software.\n\nModule| License  \n---|---  \nNQC / WebNQC| Mozilla Public License 2.0  \nNQC example code by D. Baum and R. Zurcher| Freeware License  \nall others WebPBrick modules| GNU GPLv3  \n  \n## Released versions\n\nPlease find the CHANGELOG here. Please also note that WebPbrick.com may not be\nup-to-date with this repository on GitHub.\n\n## Disclaimer\n\nLEGO\u00ae is a trademark of the LEGO Group of companies which does not sponsor,\nauthorize or endorse this project.\n\n## About\n\nWeb-based IDE for programming the LEGO Mindstorms RCX using NQC with modern\ntechnologies\n\nwww.webpbrick.com\n\n### Topics\n\nprogramming robotics web-ide webassembly wasm lego mindstorms firmware-tools\nlego-mindstorms nqc webserial webusb-api mindstorms-rcx\n\n### Resources\n\nReadme\n\n### License\n\nGPL-3.0 license\n\nActivity\n\n### Stars\n\n6 stars\n\n### Watchers\n\n2 watching\n\n### Forks\n\n3 forks\n\nReport repository\n\n## Releases 1\n\nInitial release: release version 0.1.0 Latest\n\nApr 14, 2024\n\n## Packages 0\n\nNo packages published\n\n## Languages\n\n  * JavaScript 98.2%\n  * Other 1.8%\n\n## Footer\n\n\u00a9 2024 GitHub, Inc.\n\nYou can\u2019t perform that action at this time.\n\n", "frontpage": false}
